INSERT INTO materials (type, subtype, name, description, link, created) VALUES('Bitcoin', 'Learn', 'Bitcoin Mining Explained Like You are Five: Part 1 - Incentives','It’s fairly easy to use standard cryptographic tools, like digital signatures, to “prove” ownership of something. I can prove I own one bitcoin by presenting a valid digital signature. I can also sign over ownership of that bitcoin to you by attaching your bitcoin address to it before signing. The problem we run into, however, is that there is no way to know whether I also signed over ownership of that same coin to someone else (or even to another address controlled by myself) before transferring it to you. Since bitcoins are digital, they are not scarce and can be copied ad infinitum. Any digital currency that doesn’t tackle this “double spend” problem, will be destroyed by hyperinflation on day one.','https://chrispacia.wordpress.com/2013/09/02/bitcoin-mining-explained-like-youre-five-part-1-incentives/',NOW());
INSERT INTO materials (type, subtype, name, description, link, created) VALUES('Bitcoin', 'Learn', 'Bitcoin Mining Explained Like You are Five: Part 2 - Mechanics','In this post we will take more a technical look at the cryptography involved and how it is used to secure the network.','https://chrispacia.wordpress.com/2013/09/02/bitcoin-mining-explained-like-youre-five-part-2-mechanics/',NOW());
INSERT INTO materials (type, subtype, name, description, link, created) VALUES('Bitcoin', 'Learn', 'Bitcoin Explained Like You are Five: Part 3 - Cryptography','If you’re reading this, I’m going to assume you have limited knowledge of cryptography. So instead of jumping right into digital signatures, I’m going to start by providing a broad introduction to cryptography. Hopefully you’ll learn not just how Bitcoin works, but also how to stay safe on the internet by keeping your private information away from prying eyes.','https://chrispacia.wordpress.com/2013/09/07/bitcoin-cryptography-digital-signatures-explained/',NOW());
